<br>
<br>
  I have decided to write to you with my personal opinion on my good friend of two years, Dirfrops (Russ). I started Firiona Vie the same day the server went live In October of 2001. I created the Council of Silver Griffons. For some of you that do not know of us, that is because we died out sometime by the end of 2002. I will get to that later. I met Dirfrops shortly after the server went live and he was one of the founding members of the Council of Silver Griffons. I knew then I had a good man in the guild.<br>
I talked with Russ on the phone and played side by side with him for countless hours.<br>
Russ is a good friend of mine, and I know his moral sense is strong. Those that knew me, if you loved me or hated me on Firiona you knew my word was strong.<br>
<br>
The Griffons were based on a very strong moral compass. A roleplaying guild unlike I had ever seen. We were a strong family. Unfortunately nothing lasts forever.<br>
We had begun to die off when I split up with my wife of 8 years in real life in summer of 2002. I left my faith and trust in Dirfrops to run the guild for me, and passed over leadership for a time to him. Things were stable and he led well. I came back a few times trying to resurrect the idea of the Griffons and to maintain our presence on Firiona Vie. Things transpired that kept my life from becoming stable for a time and the Griffons slowly fell out of the guild without me being around. Most of them really just wanted to move on with the rest of the server, and raid. I had no problem with that, but I was saddened by it. One of the reasons I decided to leave Firiona Vie for good.<br>
<br>
My point is, I trust Russ, and he was there for me in times of need, be it in real life, or in the game holding a high responsibility and honor. I knew Kajiin for a little while, when he tried to enter our guild. As soon as he entered, he began a life of crime, and was quickly expelled by my character &lt;Gavin&gt; but Dirfrops like me has compassion, and the whole thing was in question, but when I gave an order, I gave an order.<br>
Russ maintained some friendship with him and that is where this all falls into place.<br>
Kajiin would like to play Mr. Innocent on here I am sure, but rest assured, the guy has lied even to me, who was his Guidleader. Russ is not nor ever would be like that.<br>
Besides he has nothing to gain anymore in Everquest. I got him hooked to another game and he has been playing it with me.<br>
<br>
To all my old friends, foes, I will close with goodbye and I wish you all good luck in your new adventures. If anyone wants to drop me a line sometime or find out where Gavin Steelheart’s decent is currently, don’t hesitate to email me.<br>
<br>
Lord Gavin Steelheart (Retired) <br>
Former Leader of the COSG<br>
<br>
(And yes Gavin still misses you Air )</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
