<br>
In the end, I haven't the slightest idea who I've been dealing with both before, during, and after the scam.  I'm not sure how many people have played the Dirfrops character, and quite honestly, I don't care.  My goal really isn't to blacklist anyone forever, but to hold a person accountable for their actions.  If indeed this is a situation involving account sharing, then there are two victims here, and I appreciate the original owner making amends.  If it is a different situation altogether, then I feel all is not well in la la land for whoever is playing this account, and I pity them.  Either way, my hands are washed of it, and I'm thankful to have gotten paid back in one form or another.  However, again, to whomever was playing Dirfrops last night, thank you for your follow-up and follow-through.  I appreciate you righting the wrong.<br>
<br>
As to the community at large, I have no clue what to tell you, other than don't be as stupid as I was.  Don't trust anyone.  If you're going to do X-server trades, I don't care if the person phones you in real life, gives you a urine specimen, or their mother's maiden name - do the transfer in small increments and do it with caution.  Assume nothing.  I sure learned that lesson.<br>
<br>
Take care.<br>
<br>
Kruggan/Grixx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dirfrops>dirfrops</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 1:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3919.topic&index=165>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Situation resolution</span><hr size=1> Thank you for your final statement on the authenticity of my pledge to you and the others reading this board.<br>
<br>
Only four people, strike that five, have ever played this character.<br>
<br>
Gavin Steelheart (used me for transports)<br>
<br>
Boleorn (used me for transports and P-leveling his shaman Jahvert)<br>
<br>
Belas (I am pretty sure it was Belas), but I gave him access to my character once, and that was to get me the heck out of PoInnovation when my power went out on a raid...if it was Belas, he only got on Dirfrops once)<br>
<br>
Kajinn (plain just used me, in the most horrific sense)<br>
<br>
And of course myself.<br>
<br>
I have played other people's characters without sin, but have never played two characters at once because my other computer runs Linux (/grin).<br>
<br>
What have I learned of this lesson?  Fortunately Kruggan stated it all for me.  Don't ever trust anyone.  You take a big risk in giving someone access to a character...loss of reputation, items, monies, or complete banning altogether.  Just make sure that before you let someone on you, make sure they are wearing a 'raincoat' or you may regret it for the rest of your life (or the life of that character.<br>
<br>
There is a 1% chance that you ever see Dirfrops on this message board again.  There is 0% chance that you will ever see Dirfrops Mildrethriel on EQ1...I have uninstalled EQ from my machine (thus freeing up a precious 3 gigs of space, heh), and all his passwords are changed.  I will not delete this character for fear that someone might recreate him once the name is freed up on this server.<br>
<br>
He is dead, let him rest.<br>
<br>
For those who knew the real Dirfrops, thanks for all the fun.  For those who were harmed by the fake Dirfrops, I am sorry.<br>
<br>
And finally...Dirfrops...where the hell did that name come from?<br>
<br>
DIR ector of FR anchise OP eration S<br>
<br>
which is my title for the company I work for =)<br>
<br>
In the parting words of Pink Floyd...<br>
<br>
Goodbye Cruel World, I'm leaving you today.<br>
Goodbye, Goodbye, Goodbye.<br>
Goodbye all you people, there's nothing you can say<br>
To make me change my mind.<br>
